        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-09-05 03:33:54.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-1816 scrub: OI scrub skips new created objects for once",
        "message": "LU-1816 scrub: OI scrub skips new created objects for once\n\nFor accelerating OI scrub, it will skip the objects which are new\ncreated after the latest MDT mount and marked as I_LUSTRE_NOSCRUB.\nBut if the object with I_LUSTRE_NOSCRUB is used/cached in RAM for\nvery long time, then OI scrub has no chance to process it even if\nthere has been inconsistency happened until the MDT remount.\n\nSo as compromise, the OI scrub will skip the new created objects\nfor once only when the first accessing.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <yong.fan@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I560d7d851e3430326d24ec74154bb2a99f80b737\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
